<div type="original">
<pb f="1r" n="1" xml:id="pb-orig-1r-1" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1"/><lb n="1" xml:id="l-1"/>
<ab><vg:suppliedMilestone type="open"/>Estampes et tableaux modernes.</ab>
<vg:whiteline/><lb n="2" xml:id="l-2"/>
<ab>Ancienne maison Vincent van Gogh.</ab><lb n="3" xml:id="l-3"/>
<ab>Fournisseur des cabinets de LL. MM. le Roi et la Reine.</ab><lb n="4" xml:id="l-4"/>
<ab>Plaats n<hi rend="ss">o</hi>. 14 à la Haye.</ab><lb n="5" xml:id="l-5"/>
<ab>Goupil &amp; Cie Successeurs.<vg:suppliedMilestone type="close"/></ab>
<vg:whiteline/><lb n="6" xml:id="l-6"/>
<ab>den Haag 24 Maart 1873</ab>
<vg:whiteline/><lb n="7" xml:id="l-7"/>
<ab>Waarde Theo,</ab><lb n="8" xml:id="l-8"/>
<ab>Zou je eens <lb n="9" xml:id="l-9"/>willen nazien of er te <lb n="10" xml:id="l-10"/>Brussel nog een schilderij <lb n="11" xml:id="l-11"/>is van Schotel.</ab><lb n="12" xml:id="l-12"/>
<ab rend="indent">Dat is 6 Mei 1870 van hier in <lb n="13" xml:id="l-13"/>commissie gezonden, maar <lb n="14" xml:id="l-14"/>misschien heeft Oom het <lb n="15" xml:id="l-15"/>reeds naar Parijs terug <lb n="16" xml:id="l-16"/>gezonden.</ab><lb n="17" xml:id="l-17"/>
<ab rend="indent">Is dat echter het geval niet<c type="kk">/</c> <lb n="18" xml:id="l-18"/>zorg dan dat het <hi rend="ital">onmiddelijk</hi> <lb n="19" xml:id="l-19"/>naar hier gezonden wordt; 
<pb f="1v" n="2" xml:id="pb-orig-1v-2" facs="#zone-pb-1v-2"/><lb n="20" xml:id="l-20"/>wij hebben alle kans om <lb n="21" xml:id="l-21"/>het te verkoopen, maar <lb n="22" xml:id="l-22"/>er is haast bij.–<anchor n="1" xml:id="note-o-1"/></ab><lb n="23" xml:id="l-23"/>
<ab rend="indent">Ik heb het van de Zomer <lb n="24" xml:id="l-24"/>nog bij jelui gezien<anchor n="2" xml:id="note-o-2"/> <lb n="25" xml:id="l-25"/>&amp; denk dus dat het er nu <lb n="26" xml:id="l-26"/>ook nog wel zal zijn.–</ab><lb n="27" xml:id="l-27"/>
<ab rend="indent">Zeg Oom &amp; Tante<anchor n="3" xml:id="note-o-3"/> &amp; de H<hi rend="ss">r</hi> <lb n="28" xml:id="l-28"/>Schmidt &amp; Eduard<anchor n="4" xml:id="note-o-4"/> voor <lb n="29" xml:id="l-29"/>mij goeden dag.–</ab><lb n="30" xml:id="l-30"/>
<ab rend="indent">Mijn brief heb je zeker <lb n="31" xml:id="l-31"/>reeds gekregen.<anchor n="5" xml:id="note-o-5"/> Adieu<c type="kk">/</c> <lb n="32" xml:id="l-32"/>heb het goed.</ab>
<vg:whiteline/><lb n="33" xml:id="l-33"/>
<ab>Vincent</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
<div type="textualNotes">
<note target="l-1" targetEnd="l-5" n="1-5"><hi rend="ital">Printed letterhead.</hi></note>
<note target="l-18" n="18">dan dat &lt; dat dat</note></div></div>
<div type="translation">
<pb f="1r" n="1" xml:id="pb-trans-1r-1" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1"/>
<ab>[Letterhead: Goupil The Hague]</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
<ab>The Hague, 24 March 1873</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
<ab>My dear Theo,</ab>
<ab>Would you mind checking whether a painting by <rs type="pers" key="1348">Schotel</rs> is still in Brussels?</ab>
    <ab rend="indent">It was sent from here on consignment on 6 May 1870, but perhaps <rs type="pers" key="399">Uncle</rs> has already sent it back to Paris.</ab>
<ab rend="indent">If that isn’t the case, however, see that it’s sent here <hi rend="ital">immediately</hi>. 
<pb f="1v" n="2" xml:id="pb-trans-1v-2" facs="#zone-pb-1v-2"/> We have every chance of selling it, but time is of the essence.<anchor n="1" xml:id="note-t-1"/></ab>
<ab rend="indent">I saw it last summer in your gallery,<anchor n="2" xml:id="note-t-2"/> and imagine it’s probably still there.</ab>
<ab rend="indent">Bid good-day to <rs type="pers" key="399">Uncle</rs> and <rs type="pers" key="1613">Aunt</rs><anchor n="3" xml:id="note-t-3"/> and <rs type="pers" key="624">Mr Schmidt</rs> and <rs type="pers" key="1069">Eduard</rs> for me.<anchor n="4" xml:id="note-t-4"/></ab>
<ab rend="indent">You’ll have received my letter by now.<anchor n="5" xml:id="note-t-5"/> Adieu, I wish you well.</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
<ab>Vincent</ab></div>
<div type="notes">
<note n="1" xml:id="n-1" target="#note-t-1">
<ab>On 6 May 1870 a <rs type="otherart" key="5"><hi rend="ital">Seascape</hi></rs> was sent by <rs type="pers" key="1348">Johannes Christianus Schotel</rs> to the art gallery of <rs type="pers" key="399">H.V. van Gogh</rs> (Uncle Hein) in Brussels (<hi rend="ital">RKD</hi>, <hi rend="ital">Goupil Ledgers</hi>). In 1871 this work was sent on to one of the Paris branches, but it must have been sent back to Brussels at some point, since Van Gogh saw it there when he visited the city (between around 15 August and 15 October 1872; <ref target="let011.xml#n-8">see letter 11, n. 8</ref>). It is not known whether the work was again sent to Paris.</ab></note>
<note n="2" xml:id="n-2" target="#note-t-2">
<ab>Van Gogh was in Brussels in the summer of 1872; <ref target="let004.xml">see letter 4</ref>.</ab></note>
<note n="3" xml:id="n-3" target="#note-t-3">
<ab><rs type="pers" key="399">Uncle Hein</rs> and <rs type="pers" key="1613">Aunt Mietje</rs> in Brussels.</ab></note>
<note n="4" xml:id="n-4" target="#note-t-4">
<ab><rs type="pers" key="1069">Edouard Hamman</rs>.</ab></note>
<note n="5" xml:id="n-5" target="#note-t-5">
<ab>
  <ref target="let005.xml">Letter 5</ref> of 17 March.</ab></note></div></body></text></TEI>
